{
  "article_id": "GalenaWeeklyRepublican1921",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "On ",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicholas island",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", which is uninhabited, a ",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "party of sea-otter hunters",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          5
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "jru",
          "aji",
          "sanchez",
          "misfats",
          "gni",
          "cdi",
          "col",
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", landing to chance their luck, found, to their amazement, the imprint of human feet on the sandy shore—imprints freshly made.",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "They scattered in search. But, the wind shifting and commencing to blow hard, they had to regain "
      },
      {
        "text": "their vessel",
        "entity_key": "sh_nidever",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "before the maker of the marks could be found. It was undeniable, however, a human being lived on this "
      },
      {
        "text": "bleak, wind-blown island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "of sand and tall brushwood."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "On returning to ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the mainland",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "they reported the strange discovery, but nothing was done until ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a Roman Catholic priest",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "jru",
          "aji",
          "sanchez",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was so moved by the news that he persuaded ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the captain",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "of ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a small schooner",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_nidever",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "to sail with him for ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "After two days' searching he discovered this ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "lonely Crusoe",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "—the first of a new kind.",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "For he found inside a low hut of driftwood a woman more like a beast than a person.",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "She was clad in otter skins, and the feathered skins of the sea-fowl, and her companion was an otter, which she had caught very young and tamed.",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The priest",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "jru",
          "aji",
          "sanchez",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "with difficulty got her story, for she had almost forgotten how to speak.",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Many years previously "
      },
      {
        "text": ">the small tribe of Indians to which she belonged",
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "bhagroup"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "—inhabitants of "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "from time past—had been shifted by "
      },
      {
        "text": "the government",
        "entity_key": "gov_span",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the mainland",
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "As they were being taken on board, ",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her baby",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "had fallen into the sea, and she had leaped after him, and in the dusk had been given up as drowned.",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "She reached the shore, however, to find "
      },
      {
        "text": "the child",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was dead. In utter loneliness she had lived there for 18 years."
      }
    ]
  ]
}